com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management

Interface SupervisorServicesTypes

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    SupervisorServices
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SupervisorServicesStub

    public interface SupervisorServicesTypes
    The SupervisorServices interface provides methods to manage a Supervisor Service object. Supervisor services can be extensions to the vSphere Supervisor and provide services to applications running in vSphere Supervisor. They are often provided by 3rd party vendors. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.3.0.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.CarvelAppsCheckResult
      The CarvelAppsCheckResult class contains the information of a Supervisor Service version that is retrieved from the content in Carvel application package format as a result of the SupervisorServices.checkContent(com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.SupervisorServicesTypes.ContentCheckSpec) method.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.CarvelCreateSpec
      The CarvelCreateSpec class provides a specification required to create a Supervisor Service with a version from Carvel application package format (Package and PackageMetadata resources should be declared).
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.CheckResult
      The CheckResult class defines the result of the validation checks on the content of a Supervisor Service version.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.ContentCheckSpec
      The ContentCheckSpec class provides a specification required for validation checks on the content of a Supervisor Service version.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.CreateSpec
      The CreateSpec class provides a specification required to create a Supervisor Service.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.CustomCreateSpec
      The CustomCreateSpec class provides a specification required to create a Supervisor Service with a version from a plain Kubernetes YAML format.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.Info
      The Info class contains detailed information about a Supervisor Service.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.State
      The State enumeration class defines the state of a Supervisor Service.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.Summary
      The Summary class contains the basic information about a Supervisor Service version.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.UpdateSpec
      The UpdateSpec class provides a specification required to update a Supervisor Service.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.ValidationStatus
      The ValidationStatus enumeration class defines the type of status for validating content of a Supervisor Service version.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.VsphereAppsCheckResult
      The VsphereAppsCheckResult class contains the information of a Supervisor Service version that is retrieved from the content in vSphere application service format as a result of the SupervisorServices.checkContent(com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.SupervisorServicesTypes.ContentCheckSpec) method.
      static class  SupervisorServicesTypes.VsphereCreateSpec
      The VsphereCreateSpec class provides a specification required to create a Supervisor Service with a version from vSphere application service format, which shall contain the service identifier, display name and description information.
